modules.description: This module offers typed parameter parsing and configuration management for applications, converting string inputs into OCaml primitives (floats, strings), enums, file paths, and composite types (lists, tuples) with custom separators. It supports command-line flag handling, default values, deprecation warnings, and manpage generation for help documentation. Typical use cases include application startup logic for processing CLI arguments, validating user-provided configurations, and ensuring backward compatibility during parameter schema migrations.

This module manages configuration and logging for OCaml applications, handling command-line arguments, program terms, and formatting channels to enable analysis of binary program representations. It provides operations to transform BAP program elements—such as function calls, definitions, and blocks—by manipulating attributes, processing arguments based on intent, and applying program transformation passes like inserting definitions or resolving call sites. These capabilities are tailored for binary analysis, reverse engineering, and security-focused program transformation workflows.
